<dec f='include/unicode/locid.h' l='719' type='void icu_66::Locale::setKeywordValue(const char * keywordName, const char * keywordValue, UErrorCode &amp; status)'/>
<doc f='include/unicode/locid.h' l='700'>/**
     * Sets or removes the value for a keyword.
     *
     * For removing all keywords, use getBaseName(),
     * and construct a new Locale if it differs from getName().
     *
     * This uses legacy keyword=value pairs, like &quot;collation=phonebook&quot;.
     *
     * ICU4C doesn&apos;t do automatic conversion between legacy and Unicode
     * keywords and values in getters and setters (as opposed to ICU4J).
     *
     * @param keywordName name of the keyword to be set. Case insensitive.
     * @param keywordValue value of the keyword to be set. If 0-length or
     *  NULL, will result in the keyword being removed. No error is given if
     *  that keyword does not exist.
     * @param status Returns any error information while performing this operation.
     *
     * @stable ICU 49
     */</doc>
